						               													<description>A sugary glance and catch game.&amp;#10;Observe the sweets, count the colours and shapes and then take the right counters first.&amp;#10;Contents:&amp;#10;56 cards: each card has sweets on one side and a number between 0 and 4 on the other. The sweets come in 4 different colours (yellow, red, green and blue) and 4 different shapes (a dummy, crocodile, bear and sweet in its wrapping). 9 counters, of which 4 colours, 4 shapes and 1 sweet wild card with 4 colours&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Turn over the top card on the pile and place it next to the&amp;#10;pile. At this point, look for the colour and shape that appear the same number of times indicated in the card you have just turned over. Once you have found them, take the counters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When you have all stopped taking counters, the players who have guessed right earn a card to be put to one side. As there are always 2 cards to be earned (one for colour and one for shape), take the turned-over card and the card on the top of the pile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sometimes, no colour or shape appear in the required quantities. In this case, you only need to take the wild-card sweet. The player who get it, earns 2 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game finishes when there are no more cards in the middle of the table. The player with most cards wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
